  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - By reason of its scale, height and siting, the development constitutes an unsympathetic and incongruous form of development that overly dominates and competes with the original building. It relates poorly to the neighbouring properties and harms local spatial character. The development has not overcome the previous reason for refusal and is contrary to policies PL1 and IS3 of the Wandsworth Core Strategy (2016), policies DMS1 and DMH5 of the Wandsworth Development Management Policies Document (2016), policies LP1, LP2 and LP5 of the Wandsworth Publication Version Local Plan (Regulation 19 Version) (2023) and the Wandsworth Housing SPD (2016).",
    "Reason : 2 - In the absence of any compelling evidence which clearly illustrates that a mid-rise building would be an appropriate form of development at this location, the proposal is contrary to policy LP4 including modifications of the of the Wandsworth Publication Version Local Plan (Regulation 19 Version) (2023).",
    "Reason : 3 - By reason of the design, size and level of occupancy, Flats 16, 17 and 18 would fail to meet their respective minimum floorspace requirements and Flats 13 and Flat 15 would have poor level of privacy. Accordingly, the development results in substandard residential accommodation for occupiers and is contrary to policies DMS1, DMH4 and DMH6 of the Wandsworth Development Management Policies Document (2016), policies LP2 and LP27 of the Wandsworth Publication Version Local Plan (Regulation 19 Version) (2023) and the Technical Housing Standards - Nationally Describe Space Standard (2015).",
    "Reason : 4 - In dealing with this application the Council has implemented the requirement in the National Planning Policy Framework to work with the applicant in a positive and proactive manner and the Council has, as far as practicable, sought solutions to problems arising in relation to dealing with the planning application. We have made available detailed advice in the form of our statutory policies in the Local Plan consisting of the Core Strategy, Development Management Policies Document, Supplementary Planning documents and where appropriate the Site Specific Allocations Document as well as offering a full pre application advice service. However, we have been unable to seek solutions to problems as the principle of the proposal is clearly contrary to our statutory policies and negotiation could not overcome the reasons for refusal."
  ],
